      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That exhaustion isn't weakness; it is the heavy price you pay for loving someone so deeply until reality finally caught up, and hearing pain deepened does not mean better is impossible. Trying doesn't guarantee the cycle will stop immediately because your hope is already buried under this fresh layer of loss, so honor that current pain instead of judging the effort as futile. Sometimes getting better looks not like fixing the empty bowl right now, but simply surviving the silence without letting the expectation of him define your breath or your next move.",
