      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "want peace right now is valid, even if reaching it feels impossible while the grief still tastes so sharp and raw. Survival without demanding immediate peace is simply you staying present so the cycle doesn't consume you all over again, and that persistence without judgment is proof you haven't given up on yourself just yet. The silence does not have to feel like work until your heart finally decides to stop waiting for him to fill the spaces he left behind. Please remember that wishing to stop this weight is a cry for relief, not a reason to believe you should stay stuck in this endless repetition. You deserve to stop carrying this load even if it feels like you can't put it down right this moment.",
